  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"29\"><mn>29</mn></math>. The solutions to a quadratic equation in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a x squared plus b x plus c equals 0\"><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\"><mi>c</mi></math> are constants, can be calculated using the quadratic formula, which gives two solutions: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative b plus StartRoot b squared minus 4 a c EndRoot Over 2 a EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative b minus StartRoot b squared minus 4 a c EndRoot Over 2 a EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>c</mi></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>. The given equation is in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a x squared plus b x plus c equals 0\"><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a equals 1\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b equals 7\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c equals 5\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>. It follows that one solution to the given quadratic equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative 7 plus StartRoot 7 squared minus 4 left parenthesis 1 right parenthesis left parenthesis 5 right parenthesis EndRoot Over 2 left parenthesis 1 right parenthesis EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative 7 plus StartRoot 49 minus 20 EndRoot Over 2 EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>49</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>20</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, which is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative 7 plus StartRoot 29 EndRoot Over 2 EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>29</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>. It's given that one solution to the given equation can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals StartFraction negative 7 plus StartRoot k EndRoot Over 2 EndFraction\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mi>k</mi></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math> is a constant. It follows that the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"29\"><mn>29</mn></math>.</p>",
